location.address: 58/F, The Ritz-Carlton Shanghai Pudong, 8 Century Ave.

tip.text: First off, this place has no Michelin star. It was mentioned in the guide, whole different story. I've had better dumplings tbh but still good price value. Speak Chinese.

venue.name: Starfish Bloo @ W Retreat & Spa Bali - Seminyak

tip.text: Quite new, nicely built, modern feel. Go to the roof top for a beer but not the massage, cheaper and better options for that around the corner. Friendly staff.
Try the tasting menu. Spicy octopus dish followed by slightly sweet duck was high gastronomy. Lively atmosphere with music and open kitchen.
Go to Nespresso and have a free coffee. #PeasantLife
Intimate little restaurant. Try the pulled pork brioche, beef marmalade and the kingfish. Number 14 in Asias best 50 restaurants in 2016. Well deserved.
Try the Peking duck. Monday seems to be trainee night, avoid. Try the view. Need to be member or friend of. When we went it was basically empty.
Surprisingly authentic Greek cuisine with prices in a reasonable range. Great ambience with Greek music and the Santorini white washed walls and furniture. Try the Gyros and eggplant starter.
Open kitchen, lively atmosphere with good but not exceptional food. For the price however more than fair. Try the tasting menu (SGD 68).

venue.name: Palm Grill Beach Restaurant Ritz Carlton

tip.text: Don't know about the kebabs but the curries and Indian dishes we tried were great. Especially the southern Indian dishes, chicken tikka masala and butter chicken.

formattedAddress: Rooftop@#07-00, 171 Syed Alwi Rd (Mustafa Centre (New Extension))

tip.text: Big, bigger, busier, Mustafa. Escape the crowded shop levels to the rooftop: there's an excellent Indian restaurant up there!
Rent a bike and pedal until you're hungry!

formattedAddress: Along East Coast Pkwy (East Coast Park Service Rd)

tip.text: Nice brunch place in Duxton with friendly service. Eggs Benedict were great and the cappuccinos are always delicious.
Surprisingly authentic for a Mexican in Singapore. The enchiladas and michelada are amazing! Tacos are more authentic in Senor Taco though. Chijmes is a nice setting.
We had good food here and the service was alright. It is a big restaurant so some of the atmosphere is lost. Better in big groups. Outside area is recommended, at least for a pre dinner cocktail.
Tortilla eggs Benedict for the win. Cozy place that is somewhat hidden. Ideal for brunch. Cool rooftop photo opp from the bathroom window.
One of my favorite food courts. The rice chicken here is supposed to be famous but is sold out after lunch. Look for the busy stalls. In the evenings it gets much more relaxed.
Small gem with a few tables. The menu was so-so and that's why I would recommend going with whatever the daily recommendations of the chef are. We were not disappointed. Friendly and attentive staff.
Get the tasting menu, sit at the bar and watch the kitchen staff in action. Every three months Joel Robuchon is there personally. Gourmet but in a some what relaxed atmosphere.
Great food in a relaxed atmosphere unlike many other tasting menu venues. Well done also on the service side and the pricing.
Amazing villa which can be rented out fully. Direct beach access. Attentive staff, excellent chef and villa manager that can make very wish come true.

tip.text: Authentic Texan BBQ place. Try the pork chops and brisket.
New restaurant in Europaallee. Live piano music. Fresh ravioli. Great meat. Attentive staff though no surprise due to low number of guests. Has inner court yard for outdoor seating.
Friendly and simple family hotel with ski room. Has wifi. Limited parking for cars.
Try the bravas, ham croquetas and morcilla. Relaxed atmosphere and outdoor seating.
Try the thermal baths and rent one of the bungalows. Rustic style but one of the best in/near Manizales. During the Ferias in January you will spot bullfighters here who stay in the hotel.

formattedAddress: Kilometro 5 Antigua via al Nevado La Enea, 170017

tip.text: Part of the Leading Hotels of the World. Smaller and more private than Santa Teresa and Santa Clara. Concierge is very helpful, even if you must ask twice sometimes. Try restaurant Alma!

tip.text: Excellent new restaurant in Manizales. The chef comes from Vino y Pimienta and prepares food to share. Try everything.

tip.text: Try the fish of the day with coconut rice, simple but hits the spot every time. Best spot on playa blanca.
Authentic and traditional seafood with spectacular views. Must visit place in Cartagena.

location.address: Fuerte de San Sebastián del Pastelillo
formattedAddress: Fuerte de San Sebastián del Pastelillo

tip.text: Try the Schnitzel.
Obviously you pay a little extra for the view, but the food is excellent too. Simple 3-4 course menu in the evening is welcoming.
Gourmet restaurant not to be missed in Zurich. Wonderful tasting menu. Organic food concept, almost perfectly executed.
Only for hotel guests. Amazing view and spectacular sunsets. Try the mojito.
Mind blowing combinations. Try the tasting menu. Worth every penny and 2* well deserved.
Try the shake menu/course and half a portion of nigiri on the side. Service was a bit slow and unattentive. Great Japanese food and ambience though!
Possibly the best Turkish bath in Istanbul, the Sultan used to get his scrub on here so 'nuff said. Fully renovated in 2010. As a male you can ask to be washed in the 'Sultan's corner'.

location.address: Cankurtaran Mh. Bab-ı Hümayün Cd. No:1, Sultanahmet, Fatih
formattedAddress: Cankurtaran Mh. Bab-ı Hümayün Cd. No:1, Sultanahmet, Fatih

tip.text: Sparkling new yacht harbour with all the facilities the jetset could want. Still partly under construction but up an coming. Stones throw away from Kotor and Budva which are Montenegro must visits.
Hidden gem, just keep following the alleys until you get there. Probably not as authentic as it was once upon a time but worth a visit. Scaloppine al limone was excellent.
One of the best steak restaurants in Zurich. Great views and friendly service. Come for dinner, drinks or in between and enjoy the chic interior and elegant atmosphere.
Let the games begin. Probably the beats public viewing in Zurich for the 2014 World Cup.
Best Mexican in Zurich, by miles. Order a Negra Modelo or Margarita and enjoy. Everything is great and as authentic as it may get here. Try sopa azteca, huarache azteca or the tacos al pastor.
Be nice to the pretentious entrance staff, they are just looking for some love. Once on top enjoy the nice view. Too many working girls and substance abuse for my taste though.
Due to the spectacular decor, excellent service and audacious food probably a must-go-to-place when in Dubai. Try the Gold Souk drink on the side. 👌

It seems like this place has more waiters than people and still the service is subpar, or maybe because of it. When we were there half of the roses on the menu were not available. Nice setting though.

tip.text: Cozy bar on Langstrasse with the right sympathies.
The service is so god awfully slow that I could have brewed my own beer faster.
The Badstube has one Michelin Star, located outside of Zurich.
